Anna Bonate, from the [global network Working to Improve Maternal Health (WIM]) Women’s Health Training Organization, discussed women’s post-abortion experiences and the benefits of women’s support groups as a way to cope. “The opportunity to share the experience in a safe atmosphere [allowed women to say] how they feel…and talk about the judgments they received from their friends and families about the abortion,” she said. Funmi Salisu from STOP[] talked about illiterate and disadvantaged women and how do not often have knowledge of post-abortion contraception. She said, “We have had issues for clients not knowing that they have the right to a medication termination and we need to educate people so they know about their rights.” Janeen Mair, from International Forum for Engaged Engagement(city), discussed the problem of stigma in some countries. “In Uganda, there’s a lot of stigma, but not only stigma for women; stigma for midwives.
